claim.claim-text:
A catheter assembly comprising:
an inner needle having a blade surface at a distal end;
a catheter through which the inner needle is inserted;
a catheter hub through which the inner needle is inserted and which is fixed to a proximal end of the catheter;
a valve which has a pair of inclined portions close to each other in a distal direction, an end surface provided at distal ends of the pair of inclined portions and extending in a width direction, and a slit formed along a longitudinal direction of the end surface, and is provided in an internal space of the catheter hub; and
an opening member which is provided in the internal space, is formed in a tubular shape having a space portion inside, is located closer to a proximal side than the valve in an initial state, and moves in the distal direction to open the valve,
wherein the opening member has a side hole that causes the space portion to communicate with an outside of the opening member, and
the side hole is located closer to a distal side than a most proximal end of the slit in a state where the valve is opened.
